{"cursor":"5583","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n'Roland Lethem' (born 1942) is a Belgian filmmaker and writer.\n\nInfluenced at his beginnings by BuÃ±uel, Cocteau, the surrealists and by the\nJapanese cinema (Seijun Suzuki, IshirÅ Honda, KÅji Wakamatsu, Yoko Ono), stunned\nby the Festival of the film expÃ©rimental of Knokke in 1967 and by May 1968,\nRoland Lethem wants to push the people to look at the things of which they say\nthey are freed, it's to say to place them in front of their responsibilities.\nEven if sometimes the results leaves much to be desired, the idea of each one of\nhis films is seductive and exemplary. A fact is certain, his films are\ndisturbing, they are sometimes unpleasant to look at. The narcissistic and\nprovocative play of the debuts turned itself into direct, visual, and verbal\ninsult, and in slandering. His dream was one moment to be able to film the\nintimate life of the pope or the sexual plays of the Belgian sovereigns. Through\nviolence, pornography and cruelty of some scenes, Roland Lethem is a gentle,\ngenerous man with of a lot of humour. The work of Roland Lethem evolves, becomes\npolitical, ecological. La Ballade des amants maudits (The Ballad of the cursed\nlovers, 1966) or La FÃ©e sanguinaire (The Bloodthirsty Fairy, 1968) still tell\nstories. Les Souffrances d'un oeuf meurtri (The Sufferings of a ravaged Egg,\n1967), poem of love in several parts (Ãtoiles/Stars, Corps/Bodies,\nHymen/Marriage or Hymen (ambiguous in French), Oeuf/Egg) dedicated to all who\nconceive and to all who are conceived, irresistibly makes you think at the\nHistoire de l'oeil (Story of the Eye, 1928) of Georges Bataille.\n\nSome of the titles of his films include [[Le Saigneur est avec nous]] and [[Le\nsexe enragÃ©]]. There are several thorough studies published on his films\n(Cinema/London, Skoop/Amsterdam) and Bandes de cons! (Bunch of Assholes!, 1970),\nhis most famous film, was the subject of a seminar at the University of\nAmsterdam.\n\nHe frequently collaborated with Jean-Pierre Bouyxou and Jio Berk.\n","linknr":115,"url":"Roland_Lethem","recorded":1375059555,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Roland_Lethem&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Roland_Lethem&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/f/f4/Ambox_content.png","/wiki/Wikipedia:Biographies_of_living_persons","/wiki/Wikipedia:Citing_sources","/wiki/Wikipedia:Verifiability","/wiki/Wikipedia:Reliable_sources","/wiki/Defamation","/wiki/Belgium","/wiki/Filmmaker","/wiki/Luis_Bu%C3%B1uel","/wiki/Jean_Cocteau","/wiki/Surrealists","/wiki/Seijun_Suzuki","/wiki/Ishir%C5%8D_Honda","/wiki/K%C5%8Dji_Wakamatsu","/wiki/Yoko_Ono","/wiki/Georges_Bataille","/w/index.php?title=Le_Saigneur_est_avec_nous&action=edit&redlink=1","/w/index.php?title=Le_sexe_enrag%C3%A9&action=edit&redlink=1","/wiki/Jean-Pierre_Bouyxou","/w/index.php?title=Jio_Berk&action=edit&redlink=1","#Awards","#References","#Reviews_and_commentary_on_his_work_in_periodicals","#in_Books","#External_links","/w/index.php?title=Roland_Lethem&action=edit&section=1","/w/index.php?title=Roland_Lethem&action=edit&section=2","/w/index.php?title=Roland_Lethem&action=edit&section=3","/w/index.ph